---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="The Game" description="Quotient the Game interactive fiction">
  <section class="section page-shell">
    <h1>Quotient the Game!</h1>
    <p>
      Choose an option below to play, watch the full walkthrough, or open maps and resources.
    </p>

    <div class="book-actions">
      <a class="button" href="https://simpsong00.github.io/quotient-game/">Play the game</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="https://intfiction.org/t/quotient-the-game/72965">Watch the walkthrough</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="https://simpsong00.github.io/quotient-game/maps/quotient-game-map-no-spoilers.pdf">Spoiler-free map (PDF)</a>
    </div>

    <p>
      Quotient, the Game is an interactive fiction game in the genre of Zork. You embark on a secret mission starting at
      Quotient HQ. You can meet the characters, fly the Quotient Jet, or even take a Rocket to TARDIS.
    </p>
    <p>
      In the tradition of the books' Spotify playlists, the game includes a song for each room. Type <code>song</code> in
      the game to get the current room song, or type <code>playlist</code> to see your custom playlist based on rooms you
      have visited.
    </p>

    <h2>If You Are New to Interactive Fiction</h2>
    <p>
      Interactive fiction is text based. You move with commands like <code>north</code>, <code>south</code>,
      <code>east</code>, <code>west</code> (or <code>n</code>, <code>s</code>, <code>e</code>, <code>w</code>), and solve
      puzzles by interacting with items and characters.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-grid">
      <li><code>examine [item/person]</code> or <code>x [item/person]</code></li>
      <li><code>take [item]</code></li>
      <li><code>inventory</code></li>
      <li><code>look at [item]</code></li>
      <li><code>enter</code> / <code>exit</code></li>
      <li><code>fly to [location]</code></li>
      <li><code>switch on [item]</code> / <code>switch off [item]</code></li>
      <li><code>talk to [person]</code></li>
      <li><code>unlock [item] with [item]</code></li>
      <li><code>type [code] on [item]</code></li>
      <li><code>help</code>, <code>save</code>, <code>restore</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
